        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Adding A List To A Label"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "There are times that a small list of information must be added to a label. You can do this using CV's built in concat functionality."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "What does concat mean?"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "When you concatenate (or concat for shorthand) a string, it means you are taking a variable number of strings, like:"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "\"Hello\""
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "\"World\""
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "And putting them together into a single string:"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "\"Hello World\""
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "As an example, let's create the following view in Cabinet Vision:"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "DoorLabels"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "SELECT Doors.[Cabinet ID], Doors.[Label] + ' - ' + Doors.[Type] as DoorLabel"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "FROM Doors"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "For my database, that creates the following view in the Report.mdb:"
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "data": {
                "headers": [
                    "Cabinet ID",
                    "DoorLabel"
                ],
                "rows": [
                    [
                        "1",
                        "Open.1A - DF"
                    ],
                    [
                        "1",
                        "1B-L - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "1",
                        "1B-R - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "2",
                        "Open.1A - DF"
                    ],
                    [
                        "2",
                        "1B-L - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "2",
                        "1B-R - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "3",
                        "Open.1A - DF"
                    ],
                    [
                        "3",
                        "1B-L - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "3",
                        "1B-R - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "4",
                        "Open.1A - DF"
                    ],
                    [
                        "4",
                        "1B-L - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "4",
                        "1B-R - P"
                    ]
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "We can see that, in CABINET VISION, I have 4 cabinets that have 3 doors each (I basically created a cabinet and copied it 3 times). \u00a0Since labels can't create lists, we need to use this feature to get what we want, which would look like this:"
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "data": {
                "headers": [
                    "Cabinet ID",
                    "Door Label"
                ],
                "rows": [
                    [
                        "1",
                        "Open.1A - DF \n 1B-L - P \n 1B-R - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "2",
                        "Open.1A - DF \n 1B-L - P \n 1B-R - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "3",
                        "Open.1A - DF \n 1B-L - P \n 1B-R - P"
                    ],
                    [
                        "4",
                        "Open.1A - DF \n 1B-L - P \n 1B-R - P"
                    ]
                ]
            }
        },
