        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "As you can now see, all items that have a related 'Cabinet ID' (meaning a 'Cabinet ID' that is the same) have been combined, or rather concatenated, together into a single string that we can now place on our label."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Step by Step:"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Create a new report in CABINET VISION. \n \n \n Right click on the Report and select Properties. \n \n \n Create an 'Import'. \n \n \n Name:  DoorLabels \n \n \n Type:  Link \n \n \n SQL:  SELECT Doors.[Cabinet ID], Doors.[Label] + ' - ' + Doors.[Type] as DoorLabel FROM Doors \n \n \n \n \n Create a new table. \n \n \n Make this a cabinets table. \n \n \n On the comment list, select the following: \n \n \n Primary Field:  Cabinet ID \n \n \n Foreign Table:  DoorLabels \n \n \n Foreign Field:  Cabinet ID \n \n \n Display Field:  DoorLabels"
        },
